## Introducing new CORE
The Department for Levelling Up, Housing and Communities (DLUHC) relies on the data you provide to create better social housing policies and see how they’re working on the ground. Your data helps us to understand who is moving when and why, what properties they are getting and how much they’re paying. Your data directly helps us to design policies to improve housing supply and affordability, and support housing providers to reduce homelessness and ensure vulnerable people get the homes they need.

We’re creating a better way for you to submit CORE data: faster, simpler and built from the ground up with the user at the centre. We now want forward-looking organisations to help perfect our new service.

New CORE is ready to accept your data for 2021/22 and 2022/23, and you can get early access before everybody else.

Have you felt frustrated with submitting CORE logs in the past? Want to find out how the new service could help you? Here are a few reasons why you might want to start using new CORE today.
